latestPosts.caption:
Oh what a day! What a party! IT WAS ELECTRIFYING! ⚡️ @hyroxindia @hyroxworld 

Only got 3 weeks to train for this but like @nsingh80 said - We’ve been training for this our entire lives! 😉 Okay, maybe not 😅 

Idea was to go out there and have fun and oh SO much fun was had! 🥳 Thoroughly enjoyed each and every moment of being there - endured the pain and came out dancing! 💪

Couldn’t have done this without my crazy tribe - some who came just to cheer us and some who stayed back after their races to keep my spirits high.  @aamnaa1 @shaifali_n @johaisohay @angad_singh05 @srishtichawla06 - THANK YOU! ❤️🤗

Special points to @karanchandhiok to have FINALLY made it on time for one of my races. 🤪

Still riding on this high and cannot wait to do this again! 🎉 @hamidahmed77 @iamrohitpathak - Let’s goooo!! 🔥

“The wound is where the light enters you.” - Rumi

Tigers lick themselves primarily to groom and clean their fur, using their rough, barbed tongues to remove dirt, loose fur, and even parasites, similar to domestic cats Their saliva also has antiseptic properties which can help heal wounds when they lick themselves after injuries

We’ve often heard the saying ‘an apple doesn’t fall far from the tree’ - this Tigress proved that and how!!! Daughter of Ravan, the largest Tiger in Satpura, Bachchi was certainly the largest Tigress we’ve ever encountered in the wild. And just like her father, she loves to haunt the meadows of the Reserve, these grasslands where she blends in so beautifully 🐅

latestPosts.caption:
3 benefits why highknees with resistance band :- 

1:- Cardiovascular fitness: High knees are a dynamic exercise that elevates your heart rate, promoting cardiovascular endurance. Adding a resistance band increases the intensity, making your heart work harder and improving overall cardiovascular fitness.

2:- Lower body strength: High knees target and strengthen the muscles in your lower body, including your quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves. The resistance band adds extra resistance, making these muscles work harder and promoting greater strength gains.

3:- Core engagement: Performing high knees with a resistance band requires you to engage your core muscles to maintain stability and balance. This helps strengthen your abdominal muscles, obliques, and lower back, enhancing overall core strength and stability.

Dm to start your fitness journey today , you are just one step away ..

What do you think of new year resolutions? 😇

Honestly, there have been years I’ve kept them and not been able to follow through and years I’ve fulfilled my promises to myself. This year however is going to be different for me. 

To 2023, I just want to say - I’m ready for what you’ve got in store and whatever it might be, I shall embrace it with open arms. Less resistance, more acceptance because I’ve truly come to believe that whatever is yours will make its way to you, whether good or bad, positive or negative. We can either crib and complain about it or just accept it with the knowledge that this is mine to take and make the most of. 💫

Here’s to 2023 being the year you wish it to be 🥂. Happy new year everyone! ❤️
